Helped by brisk industrial activity, South Korea's  jobless rate slid in the three months to March to 3.1 percent, down 0.1  percentage point from the same period last year, the National Statistical  Office (NSO) said Thursday.
It was the first quarterly drop since December 1991, NSO officials said.
The manufacturing sector put on 0.6 percent more workers, reversing three  years of losses.
The nation's total work force increased by 4.5 percent from a year ago to    19.63 million, the highest level in six years.
